                            <comment id="17842902" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 2 May 2024 09:15:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;maybe important to add that I see the exact same test method failing in trunk too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17842995" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 2 May 2024 14:55:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;5.0 patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3285&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3285&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
trunk patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3286&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3286&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17842999" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 2 May 2024 15:12:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For posterity, the problem here was &lt;tt&gt;shouldNotWarnOrFailOnIndexQuery()&lt;/tt&gt; not waiting for the indexes to be queryable. To reproduce locally, you can add...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;try {
    TimeUnit.SECONDS.sleep(3);
} catch (InterruptedException e) {
    throw new RuntimeException(e);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...to &lt;tt&gt;StorageAttachedIndex#getInitializationTask()&lt;/tt&gt; before its return statement.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17843000" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 2 May 2024 15:13:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, +1 when CI is happy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17843033" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 2 May 2024 18:03:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CI results look good for 5.0 ( &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13068606/13068606_ci_summary.html&quot; title=&quot;ci_summary.html attached to CASSANDRA-19612&quot;&gt;ci_summary.html&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ) and trunk ( &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13068607/13068607_ci_summary-1.html&quot; title=&quot;ci_summary-1.html attached to CASSANDRA-19612&quot;&gt;ci_summary-1.html&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ). Moving to commit...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
